[We see so much cholera in underdeveloped parts of the world. The story is
always the same; poor sanitation, contaminated food products, lack of
education of the populace, health ministers expressing frustration at the
publics failure to comply with recommendations. Let's hear from the experts
about their view of what can be done to have the most immediate impact on
the incidence of cholera worldwide. - Mod.ES
